I called the place to discuss my dissatisfaction with the manager but I was told he or she was unavailable. If you are expecting food to take close to or MORE than an hour, it would be nice for the customer to be informed so that we can have the option of getting food elsewhere where delivery takes 20-30 minutes to get to you on average.

Went in on a satirday afternoon excited to try a new mexican restaurant.  My husband ordered the chili rellenos which he gets at every meican place and i opted for the shrimp veggies soup b.c i saw it being carried out and it was in a red flavorful looking broth. 2 other 2 tops besides us.1 hour later still no food. 1 hr 10 mins it comes out cold. By now werestatving so we were happy to dig in.  It was ice cold. And sooooo bland all of the salt pepper and lime is in the world could not fix it The soup which was in a deep red broth with at least six different vegetables tasted like hot tap water

Food was ok. Better than Taco Bell, the service on the other hand was non-existent. We went on a weekday at dinner time and there was only one other person in the restaurant. We were seated, handed menus and gave drink orders. After about 15 minutes the server came over with my wife's drink, but not mine. I had to remind her. She brought it then went back to eating and playing on her phone. We still haven't decided on what to order so I wasn't too upset about that. However, after another 15 minutes she came back for our orders. We gave them to her and I another drink order then a solid 40 minutes until we saw her again with out food. Now if everything came out steaming hot I would say the wait was due to a freshly made meal. It was about room temperature. So either she was too busy on her phone to check if our order was ready or the service as a whole is just poor. Food is one thing,we all have our likes and dislikes. Yet, after years of experience in the food industry customer service is always number 1. It's always what is remembered. This is all I will remember from my experience here. Being forgotten in an empty restaurant.
